Privacy Policy for Home Inventory, Food, Shopping
At Home Inventory, Food, Shopping, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our app and related services.
1.
Information We Collect
Email Address
: We collect your email address to allow you to sign in to your account from different devices and securely store your data in the cloud.
First and Last Name
: If you sign in using your Google account, we may collect your first and last name. This information is only used to facilitate communication with you.
Pictures
: Our app allows you to add pictures of your products for convenience, and these pictures are stored on our servers.
2.
How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
To provide account management and sign-in functionality across devices.
To store your data securely in the cloud.
To improve your experience by allowing you to upload pictures of products and manage your inventory.
For communication, when necessary, using your provided name and email.
3.
Data Sharing
We do not sell your personal data. However, we share certain information with the following third parties:
Google Cloud Firestore
: We use Google Cloud Firestore to store your data securely.
Firebase Crashlytics and Google Analytics
: These services help us with diagnostics, performance, and crash analysis to improve the quality of our app.
RevenueCat
: We use RevenueCat to manage in-app purchases and subscriptions. RevenueCat may collect and process information related to transactions, including subscription status and purchase details, to ensure the proper functioning of subscriptions within the app. For more details, please refer to RevenueCat's
Privacy Policy
.
4.
Data Retention
We retain your data as long as you have an account or continue to use the app. If you wish to delete your data, you can:
Use the "Delete Account" button in the app settings to delete your account and all associated data.
Send an email through the "Question or suggestion" menu item in the app for assistance with data deletion.
5.
Data Security
We use the standard Google Firebase SDK to manage your data. While we do not employ special encryption, your data is protected by Firebase's security infrastructure.
6.
Children’s Privacy
Our app is not specifically targeted at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect data from children.
7.
Your Rights
You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data. You can:
Delete your account and data directly from the app.
Contact us using the contact form on our website or via the "Question or suggestion" menu item in the app for additional assistance.
8.
Company Details and Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, you can contact us at:
Company Name
: Xaltos Technologies Ltd
Address
: Gladstonos 12-14, Paphos, 8046, Cyprus
Website Contact Form
:
https://chester-sw.com/about-us/
App Contact
: Use the "Question or suggestion" menu item in the app.
